Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
undo_uniquify_partition(25.10)                  undo_uniquify_partition(25.10)

Name
       undo_uniquify_partition  -  Brings  back  the  recursion  of cells in a
       netlist and restores the master and clone association

Syntax
       undo_uniquify_partition

       [-help]

       -hinst <hierarchical_instance_name>[-preserve_routes]

       Brings back the recursion of cells in a netlist and restores the master
       and clone association.

       Note: The uniquify_partition command is used to remove the  master  and
       clone association by uniquifying the netlist.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each undo_uniquify_partition parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man undo_uniquify_partition

       -hinst <hierarchical_instance_name>
              Specifies name of the hierarchical  instance  that  is  used  to
              bring  back  the recursion of cells in a netlist and restore the
              master and clone association.  Based of the selected  hierarchi-
              cal  instance, its cell (module) is identified. All other occur-
              rences of the identified cell with  the  same  naming  format  (
              cellname_<number>) are then renamed to the identified cell name.
              That means all instances will have the same cell name and defin-
              ition  again,  thereby  restoring the master and clone relation-
              ship.

              Note:

              * You  can  specify   any   hierarchical   instance   with   the
                undo_uniquify_partition command.

              * Any  hierarchical  instance  with  R0 orientation can become a
                master.

              * The name of the cells will change to the name of the  cell  of
                the specified hierarchical instance.

              *

                The  netlist  and def of the cell of the hierarchical instance
                name specified with the undo_uniquify_partition  command  will
                be copied in all hierarchical instances.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -preserve_routes
              Preserves the routes during undo_uniquify_partition.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The  following command brings back the master and clone association for
       the cell name associated with I2/p2:

       undo_uniquify_partition -hinst I2/p2

